			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nAdds internal tracking of images dragged inside the TinyMCE editor and special-case drop handling: when an internally dragged IMG is dropped, its saved HTML is inserted at the drop point, the original is removed, caret restored, and Joplin change/undo events are triggered to avoid base64 pasting.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Image drag-and-drop handling** <br> `packages/app-desktop/gui/NoteEditor/NoteBody/TinyMCE/TinyMCE.tsx`|Adds `internalDraggedImageRef` and `internalDraggedImageHtmlRef`; registers editor `dragstart`/`dragend` handlers to capture IMG elements; enhances `drop` handling to insert saved image HTML at drop location, remove original node (and empty wrappers), restore caret, and trigger Joplin change + undo step. Removes a ScrollIntoView override and related comments; preserves previous `props_onDrop` fallback when no internal image is detected.|\n\n## Sequence Diagram(s)\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant TinyMCE as TinyMCE Editor\n    participant DOM\n    participant Joplin as Joplin Core\n\n    User->>TinyMCE: dragstart on IMG\n    TinyMCE->>TinyMCE: save IMG element & HTML (refs)\n    User->>TinyMCE: drop at location\n    TinyMCE->>TinyMCE: detect internalDraggedImageRef\n    TinyMCE->>DOM: insert saved image HTML at drop point\n    TinyMCE->>DOM: remove original IMG and empty wrapper if present\n    TinyMCE->>TinyMCE: restore caret position\n    TinyMCE->>Joplin: emit change event with undo step\n    TinyMCE-->>User: drop handled (prevent default)\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 6</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (6 passed)</summary>\n\n|               Check name              | Status 